@jimjones308 I'll be 60 in a few months. I got the reference. I was even fooled into thinking it was a Budweiser commercial at the start. But the only thing I came away with was ... "WHY????"
They burned 10 million bucks (on airtime alone) to air this effing thing. 
Again ... "WHY????"

@SailorDonut 
I mean...I've been that nerdy fan for more than 40 years. Nothing about Disney's s0d0mizing of the franchise would make me so disillusioned that I'd get rid of the mountains of toys, books, comics, etc. I collected _BEFORE_ Disney took over. I too hate virtually everything Disney has done with the franchise, but nothing they've done to it has any impact on the attachment I have to the two near perfect condition Darth Vader head action figure cases I've owned for more than 30 years, nor the novels I purchased throughout the 1990s and early 2000s, nor the Gold Foil editions of _Tales of the Jedi_ 1-5 I purchased in 1994. 

The idea that the current b@stardization of Star Wars somehow diminishes the long-term attachment is nonsensical to me. It was wildly "uncool" for me to be as big a Star Wars nerd as I was in the late 1980s and early 1990s, so I couldn't care less how people feel about my fandom at this point, either, especially the f*ckwits running the franchise or who love Disney Wars. I certainly can't be so put off by those clowns that it ruins my enjoyment of the hobby I got into long before Disney got their filthy mitts on it.

@crazyralph6386 Actually, no. The Empire Strikes Back cost $30M in 1980 money, which in 2026, would be equivalent of ~$117M, representing a loss of almost 75% of its value... not counting all the value it had been losing since 1913. (Look up what else happened in 1913... and who died on the Titanic...)

Isn't fiat currency, "qUaNtItAtIvE eAsInG" (translation: *legalized counterfeiting),* and centralized banking just _grand?_

Thanks, *_Lincoln._*

@kevinroche3334 They exist, but they're still  old. Don't make them run, jump, do flips, get into extended gunfights or car chases.

It's the same nonsense when they show 120-pound females taking down trained military men. It's totally absurd.

Find a place for these people consistent with who they are. Don't try to make EVERY character into the mold of a military-age male. That's insulting to old people and women.
